# Environment Configuration

## Required Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose | Example |
|---|---|---|
| MONGODB_URI | MongoDB connection string | `mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/...` |
| MONGODB_DATABASE | Database name | `production`, `staging`, `ag_test` |
| SESSION_PASSWORD | iron-session encryption (32+ chars) | random string |
| SECRET | JWT signing key | random string |
| STRIPE_LIVE_SECRET_KEY | Stripe API key | `sk_live_...` or `sk_test_...` |
| MAILJET_USER | Mailjet API username | API key |
| MAILJET_PASSWORD | Mailjet API password | Secret key |
| DOMAIN | App domain for redirects | `https://artifactguesser.com` |

## Optional Variables

| Variable | Purpose | Default |
|---|---|---|
| NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL | Socket.IO server | `http://localhost:9667` |
| GOATCOUNTER_TOKEN | GoatCounter API (legacy) | none |

## Environment Contexts

### Production
- Vercel deployment
- `MONGODB_DATABASE=production` (or omitted, defaults to `production`)
- `NODE_ENV=production`
- Real Stripe keys, real Mailjet credentials

### Staging / Local Dev
- `npm run dev` (port 5000)
- `MONGODB_DATABASE=staging`
- Same Atlas cluster, separate database
- Can use Stripe test keys

### Test
- MongoMemoryServer (ephemeral, in-process)
- `MONGODB_DATABASE=ag_test`
- Fake Stripe/Mailjet credentials
- No external network dependencies except artifact image URLs

## Files
- `.env` — local secrets (gitignored)
- `.env.example` — template documenting all variables
- `src/lib/apiUtils/mongoclient.js` — connection management
- `src/lib/apiUtils/mongodb.js` — database handle with env-driven name
